Lawrence Tynes has filed a lawsuit against the Tampa Bay Buccaneers for $20million in lost future earnings and $15,000 in damages . 
  The 36-year-old was in training camp with the team in 2013 when he contracted the deadly MRSA infection . 
  The lawsuit alleges that the team 'failed to disclose and actively concealed ongoing incidents of the infection among other individuals' Tynes says the infection ended his career and he was placed on the non-football injury list . 
  He and offensive guard Carl Nicks contracted the infection during a training camp outbreak in July 2013 . 
  Tynes is seeking $15million in damages and says the team did not use necessary sterile techniques . 
